For any app to be used more than the initial spurt of joy that you have on a nwely downloaded app, it is highyl importatn to broadcast notifications every now and then.
Not too many to annoy the user, and definitely not zero. In the huge list of apps, most apps seem to bury down and get lost in the apps of time (PoP reference!) 
Take whatsapp for example. If you disable whatsapp notifications, the app is almost pointless. For a couple of days youll keep opening whatsapp to look out for new messages, but sooner or later, youll tend forget to check. 